The paper focuses on the information-seeking behavior of researchers in the context of digital libraries and academic social networks, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper specifically addresses information-seeking behavior. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also highly relevant as the paper discusses the importance of digital libraries for researchers. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also relevant as the paper analyzes the impact of academic social networks on scholarly activities and identifies differences between researchers based on discipline. Finally, cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is a possible category as the paper examines the behavior patterns of researchers in the context of scholarly information-seeking.
